arch:property.oc:show_val: An arbitrary portion of the external midden that was excavated as a number of flotation samples. Because of the similarity between the separate samples only one, number 18 was fully recorded. In general the material consists of small fragments of sheep-sized bone, occasional fragments are from cattle-sized animals. Burnt bone comprises ca. 5% of the material. All the flotation samples are similar in composition and also similar to 8143 and 8159, which are other arbitrary spits in the same deposit. All of these units contain a high frequency of digested bone. Flotation sample 18 contained a few dog bones in addition to the sheep/goat. Also present was a very highly polished point made from a tarsometatarsus of a large (swan size) bird. A metatarsal of a caprine had also been worked. NR 2005: Samples 2, 9, and 12 >4mm flotation 100% sorted recorded for diagnostics and flot frags only. Samples 2 and 9 are small, otherwise similar to the rest. Last number = 244
